you suspend your [`[$m]\ \textrm{kg}`] jar and push it down so that initially it is a distance [`L_1 = [$L1]\ \textrm{m}`] from the attachments and falls at [`v = [$v]\ \textrm{m/s}`].
The attachments are a distance [`d = [$d]\ \textrm{m}`] away from each other with the jar of peanut butter at the horizontal midpoint. If the springs have an unstretched length of
[`[$uL]\ \textrm{m}`], for what spring constant [`k`] would the jar come to rest at a distance [`L_2 = [$L2]\ \textrm{m}`] from the top?


